\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 Agreeing to meet up with him was the worst mistake I could made done. Instead of us going to the beach where he told me that we would be going. He took me to one of his building that was in a remote area. We entered the building, few minutes later, he left the building claiming that he was going to get us what to eat. I waited anxiously for about an hour and he wasn\uc0{\u8217}t yet back. Looking outside through the window and I couldn\uc0{\u8217}t see his car yet. I went to the door and tried to open it. But it seems the door was locked from the outside. I became so scared, being in that big house for almost two hours now. I was so frightened, I was feeling so safocated and felt like I couldn\uc0{\u8217}t breathe anymore. I remembered that I had moved with a phone. On checking, I couldn\uc0{\u8217}t find it anywhere around the house. That\uc0{\u8217}s when I realized that I had left my phone in the car. I became even more scared to the point that I started banging the door and yelling. But I bet no one could hear me since I was in a remote control. I checked through the fridge in the apartment because I wanted some water, I got so surprised on seeing that the fridge was stocked. That could only mean that David intended to leave me there.}}\par
